	(324856, 'The Crew: Mission Deep Sea', 2021, 'https://cf.geekdo-images.com/VuBqZ1sMaDAVVHF_OEJP4g__small/img/EdacXlcFZ06YK0-ZKa0oKwL4VCw=/fit-in/200x150/filters:strip_icc()/pic5988903.jpg', 'https://cf.geekdo-images.com/VuBqZ1sMaDAVVHF_OEJP4g__original/img/jGWxczXC_VWZofeAmlO_DkB0hCI=/0x0/filters:format(jpeg)/pic5988903.jpg', 2, 5, 20, 20, 20, 2.05, 'The Crew: Mission Deep Sea plunges players into a cooperative card game unlike any other. As members of a deep-sea expedition, you and your fellow crew are on a quest to locate the lost continent of Mu&mdash;but your success depends on precision, teamwork, and a shared sense of timing.

Each mission presents a new puzzle made up of unique tasks: perhaps one player must win a specific card, while another must avoid it entirely. The trick? You&rsquo;ll have to complete these challenges through standard trick-taking rules&mdash;like in traditional card games&mdash;but with extremely limited communication. Each round becomes a tightrope walk of strategic cardplay and silent coordination.

Building on the acclaimed system of The Crew: The Quest for Planet Nine, this sequel introduces a more dynamic mission system with variable difficulty levels, a fresh deck of task cards, and improved scalability for different player counts. Whether you&rsquo;re playing as a duo or a full five-person team, every game unfolds as a tightly wound tactical dance through the depths.

